The same way we rage at mental health awareness campaigns with the catchy sayings like "You are not alone" and "let's wear green" is the same way many in the breast cancer survivor community feel w/the "wear pink for awareness"

#BreastCancerAwarenessMonth #BreastCancerAwareness

Wearing pink DOES NOT raise awareness or reflect the realities of breast cancer. Neither do cutesy sayings. They do not reflect the surgeries, treatments, medications, side effects, trauma and fears of survivors. 

We feel you fellow advocates! 

#BreastCancerAwareness
